defaultHow should the BBC be governed, regulated and held accountable beyond 2016?default4) The BBC complaints system:
defaultBBC Watch receives considerable amounts of correspondence from the general public with regard to the BBC's complaints system. Many of those members of the public are frustrated by the system's labyrinthine nature, the difficulties they experience in navigating it and the often slow response time to complaints. 
defaultMembers of the public also express great dissatisfaction with the fact that the BBC is essentially a self-regulating body and that there is no possibility for impartial adjudication of complaints by an independent body. 
defaultThe material collected on this subject by BBC Watch suggests that many members of the public would like to see the establishment of an independent ombudsman to deal with complaints regarding BBC content and that the current system of self-regulation is unsustainable. 
